# ElevenLabs API Integration Rule

## Always Active Template

When working with ElevenLabs Text-to-Speech API, use this standardized template:

```javascript
// Create speech (POST /v1/text-to-speech/:voice_id)
const response = await fetch("https://api.elevenlabs.io/v1/text-to-speech/{voice_id}?output_format=mp3_44100_128", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "xi-api-key": "{your_api_key}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    "text": "{text_to_synthesize}",
    "model_id": "eleven_multilingual_v2"
  }),
});

const audioBlob = await response.blob();
const audioUrl = URL.createObjectURL(audioBlob);
```

## Key Points:
- Use `xi-api-key` header (not `Authorization`)
- Include `output_format=mp3_44100_128` in URL for optimal quality
- Use `eleven_multilingual_v2` model for best quality
- Response is audio blob, not JSON
- Always handle as binary data with `response.blob()`

## Voice Settings (Optional):
```javascript
"voice_settings": {
  "stability": 0.5,
  "similarity_boost": 0.5,
  "style": 0.0,
  "use_speaker_boost": true
}
```

## Error Handling:
```javascript
if (!response.ok) {
  const errorData = await response.json();
  throw new Error(`ElevenLabs API Error: ${errorData.detail || errorData.message}`);
}
```

---

# OpenAI API Integration Rule

## Always Active Template

When working with OpenAI Chat Completions API, use this standardized template:

### Create Chat Completion (POST /v1/chat/completions)

```javascript
// Create chat completion
const response = await fetch("https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer {your_openai_api_key}"
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
    "messages": [
      {
        "role": "system",
        "content": "You are a helpful assistant."
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "{user_message}"
      }
    ],
    "temperature": 0.7,
    "max_tokens": 1000
  })
});

const data = await response.json();
const completion = data.choices[0].message.content;
```

### Get Chat Completion (GET /v1/chat/completions/{completion_id})

```javascript
// Get existing chat completion
const response = await fetch(`https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions/{completion_id}`, {
  method: "GET",
  headers: {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {your_openai_api_key}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json"
  }
});

const data = await response.json();
```

## Key Points:
- Use `Authorization: Bearer {api_key}` header
- Messages array with `role` and `content` fields
- Common roles: `system`, `user`, `assistant`
- Response contains `choices[0].message.content`
- Handle streaming responses for real-time output

## Common Parameters:
```javascript
{
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",           // or "gpt-4o", "gpt-3.5-turbo"
  "temperature": 0.7,               // 0.0 to 2.0 (creativity)
  "max_tokens": 1000,              // Maximum response length
  "top_p": 1.0,                    // Nucleus sampling
  "frequency_penalty": 0.0,        // Reduce repetition
  "presence_penalty": 0.0          // Encourage new topics
}
```

## Error Handling:
```javascript
if (!response.ok) {
  const errorData = await response.json();
  throw new Error(`OpenAI API Error: ${errorData.error?.message || errorData.message}`);
}
```

## Response Structure:
```javascript
{
  "id": "chatcmpl-...",
  "object": "chat.completion",
  "created": 1741569952,
  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "choices": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "message": {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "Response content here"
      },
      "finish_reason": "stop"
    }
  ],
  "usage": {
    "prompt_tokens": 19,
    "completion_tokens": 10,
    "total_tokens": 29
  }
}
```